                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/3228: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-02-03T13:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 3, 1921—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 3—8:33 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>75. Legation’s 59, January 26, 11 a.m. Inspector General customs is informed that
                    Wu will postpone further action in regard to seizure of the customs. Wu asks
                    that last year’s surplus held at Shanghai be remitted to South. Legation
                    proposes press for immediate allocation entire sum 2½ million taels controlling
                        [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] Southern conservancy with customary foreign
                    consular cooperation and for notification from diplomatic body to Wu through
                    consular body Canton.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
